Business Brief -- National Pizza Co.:
   Reserve Is Set for Coverage
   Of Losses at 12 Restaurants
National Pizza, the world's largest Pizza Hut franchisee
with 370 units, said the reserve will cover disposition and
other costs relating to 12 under-performing Skipper's
restaurants. The company owns and franchises 217 Skipper's
quick-service seafood restaurants in 12 states and British
Columbia. National Pizza said the underperforming restaurants
are located primarily in Colorado.